tnership%20with%20the%20Israeli%20Ministry%20of%20Defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQureshi%20said%20that%20Palantir%20screened%20for%20three%20particular%20types%20of%20people%3A%20people%20who%20were%20independent-minded%20and%20weren't%20afraid%20to%20push%20back%2C%20people%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-launches-anti-college-internship-for-high-school-grads-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebroader%20intellectual%20interests%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20those%20who%20were%20%26quot%3Bintensely%20competitive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Palantir%20also%20attracted%20people%20outside%20of%20tech%2C%20such%20as%20military%20vets%2C%20because%20it%20was%20looking%20for%20people%20who%20were%20not%20just%20technically%20qualified%20but%20also%20aligned%20with%20the%20company's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalantir%20and%20Cohen%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20about%20details%20about%20the%20company's%20interview%20process%2C%20and%20whether%20it%20still%20asks%20candidates%20about%20topics%20like%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQureshi%20also%20talked%20about%20how%20the%20company's%20culture%20and%20business%20practices%20were%20a%20fertile%20ground%20to%20raise%20future%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Palantir%20instilled%20founder-friendly%20mindsets%2C%20such%20as%20telling%20employees%20to%20solve%20one%20customer's%20problem%20first%20because%20that%20solution%20could%20later%20be%20expanded%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20business.%20The%20company%20also%20asked%20employees%20to%20jump%20on%20a%20plane%20and%20meet%20customers%20in%20person%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vibe%20is%20completely%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalantir%20has%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-mafia-former-employees-startups-anduril-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E39%20alumni%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20run%20the