ors%20to%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20in%20December%20told%20staff%20that%20the%20company%20cut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo-company-cut-manager-vp-roles-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evice%20president%20and%20manager%20roles%20by%2010%25%20as%20part%20of%20an%20efficiency%20drive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20started%20notifying%20affected%20US%20employees%20on%20Tuesday.%20A%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20impacted%20US%20staff%20will%20stay%20on%20the%20payroll%20for%2060%20days%2C%20but%20that%20will%20vary%20globally%20based%20on%20local%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3d1a60d-3328-46b8-8712-bce1d50da777%5C%22%3E'Too%20many%20levels%20and%20layers'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20half-dozen%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMicrosoft%20insiders%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20about%20the%20changes%20generally%20consider%20the%20effort%20to%20flatten%20management%20layers%20as%20a%20good%20thing.%20One%20executive%20told%20BI%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20managers%20who%20just%20aren't%20that%20great%2C%20while%20another%20Microsoft%20staffer%20said%20the%20company%20has%20too%20many%20levels%20and%20layers.%20These%20people%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20discussing%20sensitive%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20ended%20up%20with%20many%20layers%2C%20the%20people%20explained%2C%20because%20it%20often%20tried%20to%20reward%20good%20engineers%20by%20promoting%20them%20to%20become%20managers%2C%20sometimes%20with%20as%20few%20as%20one%20or%20two%20reports.%20Often%20those%20engineers-turned-managers%20still%20spent%20most%20of%20their%20time%20in%20the%20codebase%20and%20weren't%20very%20effective%20as%20managers.%20Having%20so%20many%20layers%20of%20management%20also%20proved%20to%20be%20inefficient%2C%20these%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20doesn't%20have%20any%20centralized%20goals%20for%20span%20of%20control%2C%20or%20number%20of%20reports%20per%2